eNCA's Heidi Giokos has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African Police Service members and employed and unemployed members of the emergency services sector have marched to the Union Buildings. They are handing over a memorandum of demands related to conditions of employment. READ: Cosatu to march to Union Buildings in December Workers are demanding improved working conditions and the hiring of more people staff. The group is also seeking an assurance that corruption and maladministration will come to an end.